Syntax : 
        initialization
        do {
              Statement ;
              update ;
        }
        while (condition);

- In do while loop, the initialization is done before the loop.
- A do while loop has a do block which contain the statement to be executed followed by the update.
- And then while with a condition ending with semicolon(;).

--Working--

- In a do-while loop, The statement of do block executed first and then condition is checked.
- If the condition evaluates true, the control goes to the do block and this cycle is repeats until 
  the condition becomes false.
